title: Grateful Dead Live at Community War Memorial Auditorium on 1982-04-09
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 01/2017
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Dire Wolf-> CC Rider, Bird Song, It's All Over Now, Loser, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, To Lay Me Down, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Satisfaction, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Good One! I like the set list but have not yet listened to this from beginning to end. The Stella Blue is not "haunting", but it's not bad! [there is a drop-out right at the end]

I cranked up the volume on this one--sounds great. Just enough audience.

Thanks for putting this in the archive!

great show in spring 82 I was at this show, saw the Syracuse show the night before.  this one was more spacy and great fun in the War Memorial in Roch.  great woman are smarter and my first Too Lay me down, the space jam out of drums is great into smocking the other one.  Great rocked out ending of show.  early Satisfaction.
